When%20you%E2%80%99re%20perceived%20as%20%E2%80%98different%E2%80%99%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20challenging%20to%20shield%20yourself%20from%20the%20biases%20of%20society%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHanan%20has%20noticed%20such%20prejudices%20impacting%20people%20in%20both%20formal%20and%20informal%20settings.%20People%20frequently%20harbour%20preconceived%20notions%20about%20Muslims%20based%20on%20their%20appearance%20alone.%20She%20has%20personally%20experienced%20hostility%20directed%20at%20her%20in%20various%20situations%2C%20including%20with%20judges%20in%20competitions%20and%20with%20job%20recruiters.%20Additionally%2C%20she%20has%20observed%20that%20teachers%20sometimes%20overlook%20the%20presence%20of%20Muslim%20students%20in%20their%20classrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20experiences%20have%20had%20a%20detrimental%20impact%20on%20the%20self-esteem%20of%20Muslim%20youth%2C%20causing%20many%20to%20withdraw%20from%20public%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Led%20By%20Foundation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ledby.org%2Fhiringbias%5C%22%3Econducted%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20determine%20if%20a%20bias%20exists%20in%20the%20hiring%20of%20Muslim%20women.%20The%20results%20revealed%20that%20there%20is%20a%20distinct%20%E2%80%9Chiring%20bias%E2%80%9D%20against%20Muslim%20women%20in%20India%20in%20entry-level%20job%20opportunities%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%2050%25%20lower%20probability%20of%20securing%20such%20positions%20compared%20to%20their%20non-Muslim%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fwatch-study-shows-evidence-of-bias-against-hiring-muslim-women%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%20%7C%20Study%20Shows%20Evidence%20of%20Bias%20Against%20Hiring%20Muslim%20Women%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20address%20these%20deeply%20rooted%20fears%20and%20anxieties%20within%20the%20Muslim%20community%2C%20this%20author%20interviewed%2030%20individuals%2C%20all%20of%20whom%20belong%20to%C2%A0%20the%20Muslim%20community.%20The%20goal%20was%20to%20gain%20an%20understanding%20of%20the%20extent%20of%20discrimination%20they%20face%20and%20its%20repercussions%20on%20their%20physical%20and%20mental%20well-being.%20The%20respondents%20were%20asked%20five%20questions%2C%20over%20the%20phone%20and%20emails%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ea)%20Could%20you%20share%20your%20personal%20anecdotes%2C%20feelings%2C%20or%20experiences%20that%20magnify%20your%20fears%20and%20anxieties%20as%20someone%20who%20is%20%E2%80%98visibly%E2%80%99%20Muslim%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eb)%20What%20concerns%20or%20fears%20do%20you%20harbour%20for%20your%20family%20members%20who%20are%20easily%20identifiable%20as%20Muslim%20by%20their%20appearance%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ec)%20Have%20you%20ever%20considered%20removing%20your%20hijab%20or%20shaving%20your%20beard%20due%20to%20concerns%20related%20to%20Islamophobia%3F%20If%20yes%2C%20what%20were%20your%20reasons%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ed)%20Have%20you%20encountered%20discrimination%2C%20prejudice%2C%20or%20hostility%20because%20you%20are%20a%20%E2%80%98visible%E2%80%99%20Muslim%3F%20Please%20elaborate%20on%20your%20experiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ee)%20What%20are%20your%20fears%20concerning%20your%20safety%20and%20well-being%20when%20you%20are%20out%20in%20public%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98visible%E2%80%99%20Muslim%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHanan%20was%20one%20of%20these%2030%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfsheen%2C%2021%2C%20one%20of%20the%20respondents%2C%20shared%20some%20interesting%20insights%20into%20the%20subject%20of%20prejudice.%20It%20has%20always%20been%20hard%20for%20her%20to%20answer%20questions%20about%20the%20hijab.%20She%20feels%20such%20questions%20sound%20more%20like%20a%20debate%20and%20an%20interrogation%20rather%20than%20general%20curiosity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20her%20colleagues%20had%20asked%20her%20whether%20%E2%80%9Chijabi%E2%80%9D%20women%20as%20portrayed%20in%20the%20propagandist%20movie%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Kerala%20Story%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fthe-kerala-story-review-propaganda-shock-value%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98The%20Kerala%20Story%E2%80%99%20Is%20a%20Propaganda%20Film%20That%20Thrives%20on%20Shock%20Value%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20numerous%20occasions%2C%20she%20had%20been%20asked%20(which%20rather%20felt%20like%20an%20interrogation)%20why%20she%20wears%20the%20hijab%20and%20whether%20her%20family%20forced%20her%20to%20wear%20it.%20Unfortunately%2C%20this%20is%20the%20situation%20faced%20by%20most%20women%20respondents%20who%20wear%20the%20hijab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfsheen%20said%20she%20had%20to%20remove%20her%20hijab%20due%20to%20anxiety%20when%20asked%20by%20the%20male%20staff%20members%20at%20the%20CUET%20exam%20centre.%20Despite%20having%20been%20searched%20by%20a%20female%20staff%20member%20in%20a%20confined%20space%2C%20she%20had%20to%20remove%20it%20again%20in%20front%20of%20the%20men%20out%20of%20the%20fear%20of%20missing%20her%20exam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENineteen-year-old%20Zeyan%2C%20a%20student%2C%20was%20compelled%20to%20shave%20off%20his%20beard%20after%20he%20was%20asked%20by%20the%20principal%20of%20his%20institution%20to%20write%20an%20apology%20letter%20for%20growing%20a%20beard.%20He%20had%20refused%2C%20but%20eventually%20he%20had%20to%20do%20it%20at%20the%20advice%20of%20his%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaima*%2C%2019%2C%20was%20also%20asked%20to%20remove%20her%20hijab%20as%20she%20was%20%E2%80%9Ctoo%20young%E2%80%9D%20to%20conform%20to%20religious%20duties%2C%20according%20to%20the%20principal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%2010%20to%2012%20respondents%2C%20including%20this%20author%2C%20were%20advised%20by%20their%20parents%20to%20either%20remove%20the%20hijab%20or%20shave%20off%20their%20beard%2C%20because%20it%20is%20unsafe%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cseen%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20Muslim.%20This%20indicates%20the%20extent%20of%20fear%20considering%20their%20children%E2%80%99s%20safety%2C%20driven%20by%20the%20impact%20of%20Islamophobia%2C%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20today%E2%80%99s%20Indian%20Muslim%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20several%20non-Muslim%20people%20believe%20that%20Muslim%20women%20are%20%E2%80%98forced%E2%80%99%20to%20wear%20the%20hijab%2C%20many%20of%20the%20respondents%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20they%20were%20advised%20by%20their%20parents%20to%20remove%20it%20out%20of%20concern%20for%20their%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExperiencing%20trauma%20for%20appearance%20and%20identity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELife%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20away%20from%20her%20family%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20has%20not%20been%20easy%20for%20Maryam*%2C%20aged%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20come%20to%20Delhi%20to%20pursue%20her%20higher%20education.%20Surviving%20in%20Delhi%20requires%20a%20lot%20of%20travelling%20and%20commuting.%20As%20a%20woman%20who%20wears%20the%20hijab%2C%20Maryam%20was%20denied%20an%20auto%20ride%20by%20a%20driver%20last%20year%20and%20was%20told%20%E2%80%9Cto%20go%20to%20Pakistan%E2%80%9D.%20This%20incident%20has%20been%20unpleasantly%20unforgettable%20for%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20an%20isolated%20incident.%20Around%2010%20to%2012%20respondents%20said%20they%20have%20experienced%20aggression%20and%20hate%20in%20real%20life%20and%20on%20social%20media.%20For%20instance%2C%20Zeyan%20had%20to%20face%20a%20lot%20of%20challenges%20at%20his%20high%20school%20where%20people%20used%20slurs%20generally%20associated%20with%20Muslims%20to%20refer%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20others%20encountered%20aggressive%20interrogation%2C%20debate%2C%20slurs%20and%20microaggression%20in%20public%20places%2C%20often%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20their%20%E2%80%9Cfriends%E2%80%9D%20and%20colleagues%2C%20as%20well%20as%20strangers.%20All%20of%20this%20has%20taken%20an%20emotional%20toll.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20prevalence%20of%20hate%20speeches%20and%20calls%20for%20violence%20against%20Muslims%20have%20affected%20their%20mental%20health%20in%20various%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuslim%20children%20%E2%80%93%20who%20do%20not%20bear%20any%20markers%20of%20being%20Muslim%20%E2%80%93%20are%20also%20not%20being%20spared%20by%20individuals%20discriminating%20against%20the%20community.%20For%20instance%2C%20there%20was%20a%20recent%20incident%20reported%20where%20a%20teacher%20asked%20all%20students%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fmuzaffarnagar-school-teacher-makes-children-slap-muslim-student-class-8909734%2F%5C%22%3Ethrash%20a%20fellow%20student%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20because%20he%20was%20Muslim.%20This%20incident%20happened%20at%20Neha%20Public%20School%2C%20Muzaffarnagar%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20student%E2%80%99s%20video%20went%20viral%20on%20August%2025.%20One%20can%20only%20imagine%20the%20amount%20of%20trauma%20this%20child%20will%20suffer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrabhjyot%20Kaur%2C%20a%20trauma-focused%20therapist%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fem%3EMarginalised%20or%20Muslim%20children%20who%20are%20facing%20aggression%20of%20any%20kind%2C%20their%20brain%20chemistry%20gets%20permanently%20altered%2C%20which%20is%20not%20conducive%20for%20a%20healthy%20brain%20development.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDirect%20aggression%20can%20be%20countered%20and%20fought%20against%20but%20it%20is%20these%20microaggressions%20people%20face%20daily%20that%20make%20a%20deep%20psychological%20impact%20on%20Muslims%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Hanan.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20are%20so%20subtle%20that%20you%20cannot%20put%20a%20finger%20on%20it%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20only%20you%20who%20knows%20it%E2%80%99s%20there%20and%20most%20likely%20it%20will%20be%20dismissed%20by%20others%20as%20us%20imagining%20these%20biases.%20I%20feel%20like%20we%20often%20talk%20a%20lot%20about%20these%20direct%20attacks%2C%20insults%20and%20aggressions%20but%20microaggressions%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20continuous%20and%20insidious.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsociety%2Fwide-range-of-fears-new-indias-muslims-have%5C%22%3EHow%20Are%20India%E2%80%99s%20Muslims%20Feeling%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFear%20and%20anxiety%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20times%2C%20Hanan%20experiences%20the%20fear%20of%20losing%20her%20loved%20ones%20to%20a%20violent%20mob%2C%20rather%20than%20fearing%20for%20her%20own%20safety.%20The%20anxiety%20over%20extended%20humiliation%2C%20which%20may%20happen%20in%20the%20form%20of%20sexual%20assault%20or%20harassment%2C%20is%20much%20worse%20than%20the%20fear%20of%20getting%20killed%20because%20of%20her%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20the%20respondents%20expressed%20tangible%20fears%20and%20anxieties%20in%20one%20way%20or%20another.%20Not%20one%20person%E2%80%99s%20responses%20were%20free%20from%20any%20mention%20of%20anxiety.%20Most%20of%20the%20people%20were%20in%20fear%20of%20being%20mob-lynched%2C%20killed%2C%20discriminated%20against%20and%20sexually%20assaulted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20the%2020%20female%20respondents%20expressed%20the%20fear%20of%20being%20sexually%20assaulted%2C%20raped%20and%20harassed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20respondents%20also%20conveyed%20that%20even%20though%20they%20do%20not%20fear%20for%20their%20own%20life%2C%20they%20fear%20for%20their%20family%20members%20and%20friends%20becoming%20victims%20of%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZainab%20S.%20Qazi%2C%2021%2C%20a%20Delhi%20University%20student%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20father%20has%20a%20beard%20and%20he%20travelled%20to%20our%20hometown%20via%20train%2C%20right%20after%20four%20men%20were%20killed%20by%20the%20railway%20police%20man.%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20sleep%20the%20entire%20night.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%2020-year-old%20DU%20student%2C%20Dania%20Siddiqui%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20matter%20how%20much%20I%20muster%20my%20strength%2C%20there%20is%20always%20a%20deep-rooted%20fear%20of%20being%20attacked%20in%20the%20public%20because%20of%20my%20%E2%80%9Cvisible%E2%80%9D%20Muslim%20identity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20respondents%2C%20who%20are%20not%20visibly%20Muslim%2C%20said%20they%20had%20wanted%20to%20wear%20the%20hijab%20or%20grow%20a%20beard%20but%20ultimately%20decided%20against%20it%20due%20to%20rising%20Islamophobia%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20be%20very%20honest%2C%20as%20someone%20who%20will%20be%20starting%20her%20hijab%20journey%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20see%20myself%20doing%20it%20for%20anyone%20else%20but%20for%20Allah%20and%20myself.%20I%20see%20the%20hijab%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20empowerment.%20I%20do%20understand%20that%20I%E2%80%99ll%20become%20an%20%E2%80%9Ceasy%20target%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20visible%20Muslim%20woman%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Areeba%20Abrar%2C%2019%2C%20an%20undergraduate%20student.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20fear%20for%20the%20year%20to%20come.%20I%20fear%20that%20I%20may%20encounter%20more%20friends%20who%20are%20or%20have%20been%20Hindu%20nationalists%20or%20supporters%20of%20ideologies%20that%20could%20potentially%20bring%20violence%20to%20my%20doorstep.%20I%20fear%20every%20time%20I%20step%20out%2C%20as%20does%20my%20family%20because%20I%20am%20the%20only%20visibly%20Muslim%20man%20in%20my%20family%20and%20locality.%20I%20frequent%20the%20masjid%20nearby%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Imran*%2C%2027%2C%20who%20works%20as%20a%20travel%20consultant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENida%2C%2020%2C%20fears%20that%20someday%20she%20might%20have%20to%20make%20calls%20for%20justice%20for%20her%20family%20members%E2%80%99%20lives%2C%20go%20out%20on%20streets%20and%20protest%20against%20the%20violence%20done%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fwont-look-good-for-business-muslim-women-face-workplace-discrimination-for-wearing-hijab%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Won%E2%80%99t%20Look%20Good%20for%20Business%E2%80%99%3A%20Muslim%20Women%20Face%20Workplace%20Discrimination%20for%20Wearing%20Hijab%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20mental%20health%20professionals%20have%20to%20say%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaur%20believes%20that%20addressing%20the%20issue%20of%20impact%20on%20the%20mental%20health%20of%20Muslims%20due%20to%20Islamophobia%20is%20extremely%20important.%20The%20consequences%20of%20hate%20crimes%20are%20grave%20in%20the%20bigger%20picture.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20might%20not%20realise%20it%20because%20it%20does%20not%20seem%20enough%20to%20shake%20us%20into%20action%2C%20but%20it%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20bunch%20of%20issues%20for%20any%20Muslim%20person%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20outlined%20two%20kinds%20of%20consequences%20of%20Islamophobia%20on%20the%20mental%20health%20of%20Muslims%3A%20Direct%20exposure%20to%20trauma%20which%20leads%20to%20stress%2C%20disorders%2C%20suicide%20ideation%20and%20inability%20to%20cope%20with%20fear%2C%20and%20vicarious%20traumatisation%20in%20which%20people%20witnessing%20violence%20will%20be%20looped%20into%20cycles%20of%20stress%2C%20without%20any%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20these%20cases%2C%20the%20likelihood%20of%20p%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eost-traumatic%20stress%20disorder%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20increases.%20Such%20a%20state%20also%20determines%20a%20Muslim%20person%E2%80%99s%20interpersonal%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaur%E2%80%99s%20Muslim%20clients%20had%20expressed%20their%20hopelessness%20due%20to%20the%20indifference%20of%20the%20majority%2C%20especially%20those%20who%20are%20their%20friends.%20This%20indifference%20adds%20to%20their%20stress%2C%20she%20said.%20This%20hopelessness%20is%20not%20individual%2C%20but%20collective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20a%20religious%20minority%20as%20well%2C%20but%20there%20is%20no%20way%20I%20would%20imply%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccompletely%E2%80%9D%20understand%20what%20the%20Muslim%20community%20is%20going%20through%2C%20but%20I%20am%20familiar%20with%20it%2C%20because%20it%20has%20happened%20to%20my%20community%20in%20the%20past.%20What%20I%20do%20is%2C%20try%20to%20hold%20up%20a%20safe%20space%20and%20create%20a%20sense%20of%20safety.%20A%20space%20where%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20feel%20the%20need%20to%20mask%20their%20fear.%20Especially%20when%20Muslims%20go%20to%20their%20colleges%2C%20offices%20or%20universities%20and%20have%20to%20pretend%20that%20everything%20is%20okay.%20I%20am%20not%20the%20expert%20of%20someone%E2%80%99s%20narrative%2C%20they%20are%20the%20expert.%20I%20am%20just%20holding%20up%20a%20space%20which%20can%20become%20a%20medium%20of%20discourse%20for%20their%20narrative%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaur%20said%20she%20carries%20distaste%20for%20any%20kind%20of%20invalidation%2C%20dismissal%20or%20immediate%20solutions.%20She%20added%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9Cpersonal%20is%20political.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnyone%20who%20chooses%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20realm%20of%20psychology%20is%20apolitical%20and%20must%20be%20neutral%20cannot%20be%20more%20wrong.%20One%20cannot%20leave%20their%20beliefs%20outside%20of%20a%20therapy%20door.%20Dismissing%20political%20experiences%2C%20especially%20in%20times%20of%20polarisation%20and%20violence%2C%20would%20be%20a%20disservice%20to%20the%20entire%20field%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20this%20fear%20is%20something%20which%20can%20affect%20the%20entire%20Muslim%20community%20psychologically%20as%20well%20as%20physiologically%2C%20especially%20%E2%80%9Cvisible%E2%80%9D%20Muslims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CVisible%20Muslims%20are%20constantly%20punished%20for%20their%20self-expression.%20The%20majority%20is%20trying%20to%20inhibit%20what%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20self%20expression%20should%20be%20and%20that%20gives%20rise%20to%20so%20many%20interrelated%20issues%20like%20low%20self%20esteem%2C%20lack%20of%20motivation%2C%20cycles%20of%20low%20mood.%20Capacity%20to%20do%20so%20many%20things%20narrows%2C%20which%20needs%20to%20be%20taken%20into%20account.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr.%20Ruksheda%20Syeda%2C%20a%20psychiatrist%20based%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20news%20of%20violence%20makes%20Muslims%20more%20vulnerable.%20%E2%80%9CFear%20of%20violence%20can%20impact%20behaviour%20and%20emotions%20of%20Muslims.%20In%20addition%2C%20it%20can%20also%20impact%20their%20decisions%20related%20to%20where%20they%20live%20or%20where%20they%20work.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr.%20Syeda%20has%20dealt%20with%20Muslim%20clients%20who%20were%20not%20comfortable%20expressing%20their%20religious%20identity%20in%20a%20public%20place.%20They%20have%20stopped%20praying%20outside%20due%20to%20threats%20of%20violence.%20She%20has%20helped%20such%20clients%20with%20diagnosis%2C%20counselling%20and%20therapy.%20She%20has%20also%20helped%20them%20with%20creating%20practical%20plans%20on%20how%20to%20face%20inevitable%20events%20such%20as%20going%20outside%20their%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20though%20there%20is%20no%20statistical%20evidence%20which%20suggests%20an%20increase%20in%20mental%20health%20issues%20of%20Muslims%20due%20to%20Islamophobia%2C%20it%20would%20not%20be%20wrong%20to%20assume%20that%20they%20have%20indeed%20increased.%20It%20is%20important%20that%20such%20studies%20are%20undertaken%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEveryone%20has%20heterogeneous%20experiences.%20One%20person%E2%80%99s%20experience%20would%20not%20be%20similar%20to%20someone%20else%2C%20especially%20when%20their%20religious%2C%20gender%20or%20caste%20identity%20is%20different%20from%20the%20other.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E*Names%20of%20some%20of%20the%20respondents%20have%20been%20changed%20to%20protect%20their%20identity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694507404000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F03%2F25113456%2F4756525665_bd1e8f2895_b.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdenied-an-auto-ride-told-to-go-to-pakistan-the-daily-injustices-against-young-muslim-indians%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Wire%20interviewed%2030%20individuals%2C%20all%20Muslims%2C%20to%20gain%20an%20understanding%20of%20the%20extent%20of%20discrimination%20they%20face%20and%20its%20repercussions%20on%20their%20physical%20and%20mental%20well-being.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdenied-an-auto-ride-told-to-go-to-pakistan-the-daily-injustices-against-young-muslim-indians%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%8BMovies%20clashing%20on%20same%20date%E2%80%8B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694507400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103600466%2Cimgsize-48922.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fmovies-clashing-on-same-date%2Fphotostory%2F103600466.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103600466.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fmovies-clashing-on-same-date%2Fphotostory%2F103600466.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Imran%20on%20spelling%20of%20'I%20Hate%20Luv%20Storys'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694507340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103601854%2Cimgsi