%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-jamie-dimon-risk-resilient-economy-recession-consumption-drunken-sailor-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Supreme%20Court%20Refers%20Challenges%20To%20Sedition%20Law%20To%20Constitution%20Bench%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20referred%20to%20a%20Constitution%20bench%20a%20bunch%20of%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20validity%20of%20sedition%20law.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETurning%20down%20the%20Centre's%20request%20to%20defer%20reference%20to%20larger%20bench%2C%20the%20top%20court%20directed%20its%20registry%20to%20submit%20the%20papers%20to%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20so%20that%20a%20decision%20could%20be%20taken%20for%20constitution%20of%20the%20five-member%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20on%20May%201%20deferred%20the%20hearing%20on%20these%20pleas%20after%20the%20Centre%20had%20said%20it%20was%20at%20an%20advanced%20stage%20of%20consultation%20on%20re-examining%20the%20colonial-era%20provision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20in%20a%20landmark%20move%2C%20the%20Centre%20introduced%20three%20new%20Bills%20in%20parliament%20to%20overhaul%20the%20country's%20criminal%20laws.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20controversial%20sedition%20law%20(Section%20124%20A%20of%20IPC)%20has%20been%20repealed%20and%20replaced%20with%20a%20section%20on%20acts%20endangering%20sovereignty%2C%20unity%2C%20and%20Integrity%20of%20India%20(Section%20150)%2C%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20Bill%20accessed%20by%20NDTV%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhoever%2C%20purposely%20or%20knowingly%2C%20by%20words%2C%20either%20spoken%20or%20written%2C%20or%20by%20signs%2C%20or%20by%20visible%20representation%2C%20or%20by%20electronic%20communication%20or%20by%20use%20of%20financial%20mean%2C%20or%20otherwise%2C%20excites%20or%20attempts%20to%20excite%2C%20secession%20or%20armed%20rebellion%20or%20subversive%20activities%2C%20or%20encourages%20feelings%20of%20separatist%20activities%20or%20endangers%20sovereignty%20or%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%3B%20or%20indulges%20in%20or%20commits%20any%20such%20act%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20imprisonment%20for%20life%20or%20with%20imprisonment%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20seven%20years%20and%20shall%20also%20be%20liable%20to%20fine%2C%26quot%3B%20Section%20150%20of%20the%20Bill%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20other%20Bills%20--%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%2C%20which%20will%20replace%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%2C%20which%20will%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%20--%20were%20also%20introduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sedition%20law%20was%20challenged%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20last%20year%20suspended%20criminal%20trials%20and%20court%20proceedings%20under%20the%20law%20while%20allowing%20the%20government%20to%20reexamine%20it.%20The%20government%20then%20asked%20the%20Law%20Commission%20to%20review%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Law%20Commission%2C%20in%20its%20report%2C%20strongly%20backed%20the%20sedition%20law%20and%20has%20said%20it%20should%20be%20retained%20with%20changes%20linked%20to%20the%20circumstances%20of%20its%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694505600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fgv8pfg28_supreme-court_625x300_04_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-refers-petitions-challenging-sedition-law-to-constitution-bench-declines-centres-request-to-defer-hearing-4382084%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Supreme%20Court%20refers%20petitions%20challenging%20sedition%20law%20to%20Constitution%20bench%2C%20declines%20Centre's%20request%20to%20defer%20hearing%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme