i%20Was%20a%20Man%20of%20Immense%20Political%20Talent%20and%20Contradictions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F12112705%2F16566371011_2364670d4a_z.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sahistory.org.za%2Fpeople%2Fchief-mangosuthu-gatsha-buthelezi%5C%22%3EMangosuthu%20Gatsha%20Buthelezi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thepresidency.gov.za%2Fpress-statements%2Fpresident-ramaphosa-announces-passing-honourable-prince-mangosuthu-buthelezi%252C-traditional-prime-minister-zulu-nation-and-monarch%5C%22%3Ewho%20has%20died%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20a%20history%20maker.%20He%20was%20born%20on%20August%2027%2C%201928%20into%20a%20tumultuous%20global%20century%2C%20and%20into%20the%20local%20conditions%20of%20racist%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20man%20of%20singular%20political%20talent%2C%20Buthelezi%20was%20among%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20most%20influential%20black%20leaders%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20his%20long%20and%20remarkable%20life.%20Yet%20he%20occupied%20an%20anomalous%20position%20within%20the%20politics%20of%20the%20anti-apartheid%20struggle.%20He%20brokered%20Zulu%20ethnic%20nationalism%2C%20feeding%20a%20measure%20of%20credibility%20into%20apartheid%20ideals%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sahistory.org.za%2Farticle%2Fhistory-separate-development-south-africa%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cseparate%20development%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%2C%20against%20growing%20calls%20for%20unity%20under%20a%20democratic%2C%20South%20Africanist%20banner.%20But%20he%20claimed%20his%20position%20to%20be%20a%20realistic%20strategy%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20armed%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20will%20be%20remembered%20as%20the%20founder%20and%20stalwart%20campaigner%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifp.org.za%2F%5C%22%3EInkatha%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Zulu%20movement.%20He%E2%80%99ll%20also%20be%20remembered%20for%20the%20violent%20civil%20strife%20between%20his%20followers%20and%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fomalley.nelsonmandela.org%2Fomalley%2Findex.php%2Fsite%2Fq%2F03lv02424%2F04lv02730%2F05lv03188%2F06lv03222.htm%5C%22%3EUnited%20Democratic%20Front%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20African%20National%20Congress%20(ANC).%20The%20violence%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fromthethornveld.co.za%2Fviolence-and-solace-the-natal-civil-war-in-late-apartheid-south-africa%2F%5C%22%3Eclaimed%20nearly%2020%2C000%20lives%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0during%20the%20last%20decade%20of%20racist%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sahistory.org.za%2Farticle%2Fnational-party-np%5C%22%3ENational%20Party%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EButhelezi%E2%80%99s%20mother%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sahistory.org.za%2Fpeople%2Fprincess-magogo%5C%22%3EPrincess%20Magogo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20granddaughter%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sahistory.org.za%2Fpeople%2Fking-cetshwayo%5C%22%3EKing%20Cetshwayo%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20sister%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-academic.com%2Fdic.nsf%2Fenwiki%2F282741%5C%22%3EKing%20Solomon%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20was%20an%20important%20person%20in%20her%20own%20right.%20His%20great-grandfather%20was%20said%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cprime%20minister%20of%20the%20Zulu%20nation%20during%20King%20Cetshwayo%E2%80%99s%20reign%E2%80%9D.%20He%20took%20up%20this%20role%20himself%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAppetite-Power-Buthelezis-Inkatha-Africa%2Fdp%2F0253308127%5C%22%3Ein%20relation%20to%20the%20monarchy%20of%20King%20Goodwill%20Zwelithini%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20complex%20figure%2C%20Buthelezi%20(or%20Shenge%2C%20as%20he%20was%20known%20to%20many)%20enjoyed%20traditional%20titles%20of%20chief%20and%20prince.%20He%20was%20also%20rooted%20in%20Christian%20and%20modernist%20ideals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EButhelezi%20lived%20his%20personal%20life%20as%20a%20dedicated%20Anglican%2C%20with%20a%20close%20connection%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sahistory.org.za%2Fpeople%2Fbishop-alphaeus-hamilton-zulu%5C%22%3EAlpheus%20Zulu%2C%20Bishop%20of%20Zululand%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20enjoyed%20a%20long%20marriage%20to%20Irene%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timeslive.co.za%2Fnews%2Fsouth-africa%2F2019-03-25-mangosuthu-buthelezis-wife-dies%2F%5C%22%3Ewho%20died%20aged%2089%20in%202019%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20tragically%20endured%20the%20deaths%20of%20five%20children%2C%20two%20of%20them%20of%20from%20AIDS%2C%20a%20fact%20he%20declared%20publicly.%20He%20was%20taking%20a%20brave%20stand%20against%20stigma%20at%20a%20time%20when%20most%20political%20elites%20fostered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hsph.harvard.edu%2Fnews%2Fmagazine%2Fspr09aids%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20climate%20of%20denial%20around%20the%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolitical%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20political%20career%20began%20early.%20He%20joined%20the%20ANC%20Youth%20League%20and%20was%20expelled%20for%20student%20political%20protest%20while%20studying%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Fort%20Hare%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fovercomingapartheid.msu.edu%2Fpeople.php%3Fkid%3D163-574-496%5C%22%3Ein%201950%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Set%20to%20become%20a%20lawyer%2C%20and%20due%20to%20do%20articles%20with%20South%20African%20Communist%20Party%20lawyer%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sahistory.org.za%2Fpeople%2Frowley-israel-arenstein%5C%22%3ERowley%20Arenstein%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20changed%20route%20to%20take%20up%20politics%20full%20time.%20This%20was%20a%20crucial%20turning%20point%2C%20which%20he%20attributed%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nobelprize.org%2Fprizes%2Fpeace%2F1960%2Flutuli%2Ffacts%2F%5C%22%3EChief%20Albert%20Luthuli%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Luthuli%2C%20a%20father%20figure%20whom%20Buthelezi%20claimed%20as%20a%20mentor%2C%20bridged%20Zulu%20traditions%20and%20modern%20liberal%20ones%20in%20his%20role%20as%20both%20a%20chief%20and%20as%20ANC%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20South%20Africa%20was%20changing.%20When%20Buthelezi%20chose%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20politics%20of%20apartheid%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Chomeland%E2%80%9D%20policy%20from%201970%2C%20he%20initially%20did%20so%20with%20widespread%20support.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sahistory.org.za%2Farticle%2Fhomelands%5C%22%3EHomelands%20or%20%E2%80%9Cbantustans%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0were%20the%2010%20impoverished%20rural%20areas%20reserved%20for%20black%20people%2C%20where%2C%20as%20ethnic%20entities%2C%20they%20exercised%20nominal%20self-rule%20separate%20from%20the%20developed%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20ruled%20exclusively%20and%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20all%20white%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20occupying%20a%20platform%20from%20which%20he%20also%20kept%20the%20internal%20flame%20of%20political%20opposition%20alive.%20He%20did%20this%20first%20linked%20to%20the%20name%20and%20direction%20of%20the%20banned%20ANC%2C%20which%20had%20reconstituted%20itself%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F722941%3Fseq%3D1%5C%22%3Ein%20exile%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Buthelezi%20could%20legitimately%20claim%20to%20have%20blocked%20the%20National%20Party%E2%80%99s%20vision%20of%20ultimate%20complete%20ethnic%20%E2%80%9Chomeland%E2%80%9D%20separatism%2C%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.loot.co.za%2Fproduct%2Fgerhard-mare-ethnic-continuities-and-a-state-of-excepti%2Flwln-6892-ga50%5C%22%3Erefusing%20%E2%80%9Cindependence%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20KwaZulu%20territory%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHad%20he%20not%20opposed%20the%20apartheid%20state%E2%80%99s%20plans%20for%20the%20then%20fledgling%20King%20Goodwill%2C%20modelled%20on%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F2009-2017.state.gov%2Fdocuments%2Forganization%2F160146.pdf%5C%22%3Ethe%20monarchy%20of%20Swaziland%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(now%20Eswatini)%20%E2%80%93%20an%20executive%20monarch%20with%20total%20political%20and%20economic%20power%20%E2%80%93%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20history%20would%20have%20unfolded%20very%20differently.%20In%20KwaZulu%20this%20would%20have%20meant%20a%20single%20person%20in%20control%20(the%20young%20Goodwill%20Zwelithini)%2C%20beholden%20to%20the%20purse-string%20holders%20in%20Pretoria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20Buthelezi%E2%80%99s%20stand%20on%20%E2%80%9Cindependence%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20in%20the%20climate%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fevent%2FCold-War%5C%22%3ECold%20War%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmg.co.za%2Farticle%2F2013-04-15-buthelezi-to-attend-thatchers-funeral%2F%5C%22%3Econsidered%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20many%20western%20leaders%20the%20most%20likely%20and%20desirable%20black%20leader%20to%20bring%20about%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D6NKXyt5M_XY%5C%22%3Edemocratic%2C%20and%20capitalist%2C%20South%20Africa%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EButhelezi%20consistently%20called%20for%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fmangosuthu-gatsha-buthelezi-a-reappraisal-of-his-fight-against-apartheid-144212%5C%22%3Erelease%20of%20political%20prisoners%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20formed%20a%20political%20movement%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F2636898%3Fseq%3D1%5C%22%3EInkatha%2C%20in%201975%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20ensured%20its%20growth%20and%20survival%20%E2%80%93%20and%20thus%20his%20own%20%E2%80%93%20within%20the%20KwaZulu%20base.%20In%201979%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F238317279_Versions_of_resistance_history_in_South_Africa_The_ANC_strand_in_Inkatha_in_the_1970s_and_1980s%5C%22%3Ehe%20fell%20out%20of%20grace%20with%20the%20ANC%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20what%20he%20continued%20to%20consider%20both%20a%20misinterpretation%20of%20his%20objectives%20and%20a%20manipulative%20power%20play%2C%20leaving%20a%20sore%20point%20that%20endured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EButhelezi%20increasingly%20worked%20his%20own%20base%2C%20using%20media%20masterfully%20in%20a%20pre-internet%20world.%20He%20distributed%20every%20speech%20on%20a%20mailing%20list%2C%20nationally%20and%20internationally%2C%20drawing%20in%20supportive%20journalists%20and%20political%20analysts.%20In%20the%201980s%2C%20he%20drew%20finances%20for%20innovative%20and%20convincing%20research%2C%20inaugurating%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F02533958108458305%3FjournalCode%3Drsdy20%5C%22%3EButhelezi%20Commission%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20investigated%20the%20entwined%20economies%20of%20Natal%20and%20KwaZulu.%20This%20was%20followed%20by%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F3330064%3Fseq%3D1%5C%22%3EKwaZulu-Natal%20Indaba%20of%201986%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20the%20potential%20of%20a%20post-apartheid%20federal%20system%20was%20explored.%20Coming%20just%20before%20the%20political%20manoeuvres%20in%20the%20late%201980s%20and%20the%20transition%20in%20the%20early%201990s%2C%20and%20from%20such%20a%20strong%20source%2C%20it%20would%20have%20confirmed%20to%20negotiators%20on%20all%20sides%20that%20ethnic%20%E2%80%9Chomelands%E2%80%9D%20would%20continue%20to%20feature%20in%20a%20democratic%20South%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAttempts%20to%20initiate%20national%20linkages%20such%20as%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F2636898%3Fseq%3D1%5C%22%3ESouth%20African%20Black%20Alliance%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0failed%20to%20take%20off.%20Likewise%20efforts%20to%20present%20himself%20as%20a%20national%20politician%2C%20for%20example%20through%20annual%20mass%20meetings%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sahistory.org.za%2Fplace%2Fsoweto-johannesburg%5C%22%3ESoweto%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20massive%20black%20urban%20settlement%20outside%20Johannesburg.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EButhelezi%20never%20managed%20to%20escape%20the%20political%20damage%20of%20%E2%80%9Cparticipation%E2%80%9D%20and%20working%20%E2%80%9Cwithin%20the%20apartheid%20system%E2%80%9D.%20His%20association%20with%20Zulu%20ethnic%20authority%20both%20served%20and%20undermined%20him.%20When%20the%20ambiguity%20of%20his%20affiliation%20to%20the%20ANC%20came%20to%20a%20head%20in%201979%2C%20he%20was%20increasingly%20dependent%20on%20the%20apartheid%20state.%20He%20became%2C%20inescapably%2C%20part%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F02582473.2021.1895878%5C%22%3Ecivil%20war%20waged%20from%201985%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sharing%20the%20ANC%20as%20enemy%20with%20his%20apartheid%20state%20supporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20its%20part%2C%20the%20ANC%20could%20not%20accept%20another%20internal%20political%20position%20from%20internal%20structures%20not%20already%20committed%20to%20it.%20This%20especially%20once%20trade%20unions%20grew%20and%20civil%20unrest%20took%20on%20organisational%20forms%20under%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fomalley.nelsonmandela.org%2Fomalley%2Findex.php%2Fsite%2Fq%2F03lv02424%2F04lv02730%2F05lv03188%2F06lv03222.htm%5C%22%3EUnited%20Democratic%20Front%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20fully%20supported%20the%20exiled%20ANC%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20complex%20negotiations%20for%20a%20democratic%20country%20%E2%80%93%20which%20he%20argued%20made%20him%20a%20bit%20player%20%E2%80%93%20Buthelezi%20withdrew%20from%20participation%2C%20against%20the%20background%20of%20the%20raging%20civil%20war.%20He%20returned%20after%20the%20KwaZulu%20government%20had%20passed%20legislation%20that%20ensured%20the%20clear%20continuation%20of%20ethnic%20rule%20in%20the%20region.%20It%20also%20guaranteed%20that%20all%20%E2%80%9Chomeland%E2%80%9D%20land%20would%20continue%20directly%20under%20King%20Goodwill%2C%20as%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F02582473.2021.1909116%5C%22%3Ethe%20Ingonyama%20Trust%20Land%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3