Bias%20of%20Manipur%20Media%20Towards%20a%20Community%2C%20Total%20Misrepresentation%20of%20Facts'%3A%20Army's%20Letter%20to%20EGI%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F12101935%2FF3L9084aoAAReUs.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%2C%20facing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fmanipur-police-files-fir-against-editors-guild-fact-finding-team-cites-revoked-sec-66a%5C%22%3Ea%20first%20information%20report%20filed%20by%20the%20Manipur%20Police%20against%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20a%20fact-finding%20report%2C%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20it%20visited%20Manipur%20on%20the%20Indian%20Army%E2%80%99s%20invitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%E2%80%99s%20letter%20to%20the%20Guild%E2%80%99s%20president%20Seema%20Mustafa%2C%20dated%20July%2012%2C%20reveals%20that%20it%20asked%20the%20journalists%E2%80%99%20body%20to%20conduct%20an%20examination%20of%20local%20media%20reports%20highlighted%20by%20it.%20Local%20media%2C%20the%20letter%20said%2C%20had%20%E2%80%9Cbeen%20indulging%20in%20outright%20misrepresentation%20of%20facts%20that%20violate%20all%20norms%20of%20journalistic%20ethics%20and%20in%20the%20process%20may%20be%20one%20of%20the%20major%20contributors%20to%20the%20instigation%20of%20further%20violence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20signed%20by%20Colonel%20Anurag%20Pandey%20of%20the%20Information%20Warfare%20wing%2C%20for%20the%20General%20Officer%20Commanding%2C%20notes%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbias%20of%20the%20media%20in%20favour%20of%20one%20community%20and%20against%20the%20other%20community%20emerges%20clearly%E2%80%9D%20in%20daily%20reports.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Feditors-guild-fact-finding-report-manipur-media-meitei-biren-internet%5C%22%3EThe%20Guild%E2%80%99s%20own%20report%20too%20notes%20this%20bias%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20notes%20that%20Imphal-based%20media%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Coutright%20representation%20of%20facts%E2%80%9D%C2%A0may%20be%20one%20of%20the%20major%20contributors%20to%20the%20instigation%20of%20further%20violence%2C%20despite%20an%20internet%20ban%20in%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%2C%20therefore%2C%20request%20that%20an%20examination%20of%20the%20above%20reports%20be%20conducted%20to%20ascertain%20whether%20the%20guidelines%20for%20journalists%20and%20media%20houses%20have%20been%20violated%20by%20these%20media%20houses%20which%20appears%20one-sided%20and%20appropriate%20action%20be%20taken%20accordingly%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20also%20cites%20a%20few%20instances%20where%20its%20version%20of%20events%20differ%20from%20allegedly%20partisan%20versions%20presented%20by%20local%20media.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20quantum%20of%20incorrect%20reporting%20being%20enormous%2C%20the%20undersigned%20would%20like%20to%20clearly%20establish%20the%20facts%20of%20the%20matter%20through%20three%20cases%20as%20illustrations%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20illustration%2C%20the%20letter%20speaks%20of%20an%20incident%20in%20Khamenlok%20on%20June%2013.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20incident%20revolved%20around%20a%20mob%20which%20had%20raided%20villages%20of%20Khamenlok%20and%20adjoining%20areas%20commencing%2012%20June.%20The%20mob%20was%20duly%20supported%20by%20womenfolk%20who%20blocked%20Army%20troops%20trying%20to%20reach%20the%20village%2C%20so%20that%20the%20mob%20could%20go%20about%20burning%20the%20village%20unhindered.%20After%20carrying%20out%20arson%20of%20multiple%20villages%2C%20members%20supporting%2F%20those%20who%20actually%20undertook%20arson%20were%20killed%20in%20a%20retaliatory%20strike.%20It%20was%20a%20clear%20case%20of%20the%20attackers%20being%20attacked.%20Few%20amongst%20those%20who%20got%20killed%2C%20not%20hailing%20from%20the%20area%20%26amp%3B%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20were%20killed%20in%20a%20village%20of%20the%20other%20community%20may%20serve%20to%20give%20an%20indication%20of%20turn%20of%20events%20on%2013%20June.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20notes%20that%20%E2%80%9Cnotwithstanding%20the%20truth%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20newspapers%20in%20Imphal%20covered%20the%20incident%20as%20visible%20in%20some%20paper%20cuttings%20it%20attached%20to%20the%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20attached%20clips%20were%20from%20%3Cem%3ESangai%20Express%2C%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Chronicle%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%3Cem%3E%20The%20Imphal%20Free%20Press.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F12094532%2FScreenshot-2023-09-12-at-9.44.22-AM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22687%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F12094532%2FScreenshot-2023-09-12-at-9.44.22-AM.png%20948w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F12094532%2FScreenshot-2023-09-12-at-9.44.22-AM-300x130.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-672638%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22297%5C%22%3E%20%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20521px)%2085vw%2C%20521px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F12094542%2FScreenshot-2023-09-12-at-9.44.30-AM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22521%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F12094542%2FScreenshot-2023-09-12-at-9.44.30-AM.png%20842w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F12094542%2FScreenshot-2023-09-12-at-9.44.30-AM-300x230.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-672639%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20also%20made%20mention%20of%20an%20incident%20in%20Khoken%20on%20June%209%2C%20which%20it%20called%20a%20%E2%80%9Cblack%20moment%E2%80%9D%20in%20journalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Kuki%20village%20of%20Khoken%20was%20attacked%20at%204%20AM%20on%2009%20June%20by%20armed%20miscreants%20dressed%20in%20police%20uniforms.%20Three%20people%20were%20killed%20in%20the%20incident%2C%20including%20a%2067%20year%20old%20woman%20who%20was%20shot%20in%20the%20village%20church.%20A%20large%20number%20of%20Meitei%3Cbr%3E%5Cnwomen%20began%20gathering%20in%20the%20adjoining%20village%20of%20Sangaithel%20when%20news%20spread%20that%20the%20Army%20was%20engaging%20the%20attackers%20in%20a%20gunfight.%20The%20names%20of%20the%20deceased%20were%20posted%20on%20Twitter%20by%20a%20Kuki%20handle%20by%20noon%20on%2009%20June.%20Attack%20on%20Khoken%20village(Kuki%20Village)%20by%20Kuki%20militants%20%26amp%3B%20all%20those%20killed%20being%20termed%20as%20Kuki%20militants%20(one%2067%20year%20old%20woman%20%26amp%3B%20one%2070%3Cbr%3E%5Cnyr%20old%20man)%20could%20well%20serve%20to%20be%20another%2C%20black%20moment%20in%20journalism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20then%20said%20that%20the%20version%20of%20the%20incident%20covered%20by%20Imphal-based%20media%20outlets%20was%20ostensibly%20illustrated%20in%20the%20paper%20clips%20the%20Army%20attached.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F12095510%2FScreenshot-2023-09-12-at-9.54.24.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F12095510%2FScreenshot-2023-09-12-at-9.54.24.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F12095510%2FScreenshot-2023-09-12-at-9.54.24-300x184.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%