n%20and%20Maria%20A.%20Ressa%20are%20hereby%20ACQUITTED%20in%20Criminal%20Case%20No.%20R-PSG-18-02983-CR%20for%20violation%20of%20Section%20255%20of%20the%201997%20National%20Internal%20Revenue%20Code%2C%20as%20amended%2C%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20they%20did%20not%20commit%20the%20offense%20charged%20in%20the%20Information.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20civil%20aspect%20of%20the%20case%20is%20DISMISSED%2C%E2%80%9D%20Pasig%20City%20Regional%20Trial%20Court%20Branch%20157%2C%20under%20Presiding%20Judge%20Ana%20Teresa%20Cornejo-Tomacruz%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rappler.com%2Fnation%2Fnobel-laureate-maria-ressa-rappler-acquitted-tax-evasion-september-2023%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERessa%C2%A0had%20a%20smile%20on%20her%C2%A0face%20as%20the%20judge%20delivered%20the%20acquittal%2C%20said%20AFP%20news%20agency.%C2%A0%E2%80%9CYou%20gotta%20have%20faith%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%20reporters%20outside%20the%20courtroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20acquittal%20now%20strengthens%20our%20resolve%20to%20continue%20with%20the%20justice%20system%2C%20to%20submit%20ourselves%20to%20the%20court%20despite%20the%20political%20harassment%2C%20despite%20the%20attack%20on%20press%20freedom%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERessa%2C%2059%2C%20who%20jointly%20received%20the%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize%20alongside%20Russian%20journalist%20Dmitry%20Muratov%20in%202021%2C%20has%20found%20herself%20embroiled%20in%20multiple%20legal%20disputes%20that%20started%20during%20the%20tenure%20of%20former%20president%20Rodrigo%20Duterte.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20vocal%20critic%20of%20Duterte%20and%20his%20controversial%20anti-drug%20campaign%2C%20she%20has%20maintained%20that%20the%20charges%20against%20her%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3ERappler%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0were%20politically%20motivated.%20A%20US%20citizen%2C%20she%20has%20chosen%20to%20remain%20based%20in%20the%20Philippines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20after%20Tuesday%E2%80%99s%20court%20verdict%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rappler.com%2Fnation%2Fstatement-acquittal-tax-evasion-september-2023%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ERappler%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20victory%20not%20just%20for%20Rappler%20but%20for%20everyone%20who%20has%20kept%20the%20faith%20that%20a%20free%20and%20responsible%20press%20empowers%20communities%20and%20strengthens%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20share%20this%20with%20our%20colleagues%20in%20the%20industry%20who%20have%20been%20besieged%20by%20relentless%20online%20attacks%2C%20unjust%20arrests%20and%20detentions%2C%20and%20red-tagging%20that%20have%20resulted%20in%20physical%20harm%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3ERappler%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20statement%20continued.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20share%20this%20with%20Filipinos%20doing%20business%20for%20social%20good%20but%20who%2C%20like%20us%2C%20have%20suffered%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20oppressive%20governments.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20were%20the%20charges%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERessa%20and%20%3Cem%3ERappler%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20been%20confronted%20with%20five%20government%20charges%20related%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fphilippines-court-acquits-maria-ressa-of-tax-evasion%2Fa-64431211%5C%22%3Etax%20evasion%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0stemming%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20Philippine%20depositary%20receipts%20in%202015%2C%20a%20financial%20instrument%20used%20by%20companies%20to%20raise%20funds%20from%20foreign%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20they%20were%20cleared%20of%20four%20charges%20by%20one%20court.%20The%20final%20charge%20was%20heard%20by%20a%20different%20court%2C%20which%20also%20exonerated%20Ressa%20from%20any%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20particular%20case%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ERappler%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20filed%20two%20months%20after%20the%20Philippines%E2%80%99%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20(SEC)%20issued%20a%20closure%20order%20against%20Rappler%20based%20on%20the%20claim%20of%20the%20Duterte%20administration%20that%20the%20company%20is%20foreign-owned.%C2%A0Rappler%20is%2C%20however%2C%20a%20100%25%20Filipino-owned%20company%20%E2%80%93%20a%20point%20asserted%20by%20the%20newsroom%20in%20its%20appeal%20against%20the%20SEC%20order%20pending%20before%20the%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20(CA).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%C2%A0acquittals%2C%20Ressa%20and%20%3Cem%3ERappler%3C%2Fem%3E%20still%20confront%20two%20additional%20legal%20battles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERessa%20and%20her%20former%20colleague%2C%20Rey%20Santos%20Jr.%2C%20are%20currently%20appealing%20a%20cyber%20libel%20conviction%20that%20carries%20a%20nearly%20seven-year%20prison%20sentence.%20She%20is%20currently%20on%20bail%2C%20and%20requires%20court%20permission%20for%20international%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERappler%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20challenging%20an%20order%20from%20the%20Philippine%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20to%20shut%20down%20based%20on%20allegations%20of%20violating%20the%20ban%20on%20foreign%20ownership%20in%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERessa%20and%20%3Cem%3ERappler%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3Es%20legal%20troubles%20commenced%20in%202016%20following%20Duterte%E2%80%99s%20election%2C%20during%20which%20he%20frequently%20attacked%20his%20critics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20prominent%20critic%20of%20Duterte%2C%20human%20rights%20campaigner%20Leila%20de%20Lima%2C%20has%20spent%20over%20six%20years%20in%20detention%20on%20drug%20trafficking%20charges%20that%20she%20says%20were%20fabricated%20to%20silence%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWith%20inputs%20from%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fmaria-ressa-acquitted-of-final-tax-evasion-charge%2Fa-66784141%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694491257000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fphilippines-maria-ressa-rappler-acquitted-of-final-tax-evas