g%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20claimed%20success%20in%20reaching%20a%20consensus%20over%20the%20G20%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%20on%20Saturday%2C%20September%209.%20%E2%80%9COn%20the%20back%20of%20the%20hard%20work%20of%20all%20the%20teams%2C%20we%20have%20received%20consensus%20on%20the%20G20%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Summit%20Declaration%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CI%20announce%20the%20adopting%20of%20this%20declaration%2C%E2%80%9D%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20told%20the%20G20%20leaders%2C%20including%20the%20head%20of%20newly%20admitted%20African%20Union.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20G20%20Presidential%20is%20exceptional%2C%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20claimed.%20In%20a%20seemingly%20rhetorical%20flourish%2C%20the%20poster%20boy%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20apparently%20said%20India%20contributed%20to%20making%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20world-ready%20and%20the%20world%20India-ready%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20consensus%20on%20the%20NDD%20(New%20Delhi%20Declaration)%20seems%20to%20have%20come%20after%20Russia%20and%20China%20agreed%20to%20the%20specific%20language%20in%20paragraph%20eight%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20Planet%2C%20People%2C%20Peace%20and%20Prosperity%E2%80%9D%20that%20merely%20said%20%E2%80%9Cconcerning%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%E2%80%9D%20instead%20of%20%E2%80%9Caggression%20by%20the%20Russian%20Federation%20against%20Ukraine%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20previous%20Bali%20Declaration%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fg20-modi-new-delhi-declaration-consensus%5C%22%3EG20%E2%80%99s%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%C2%A0Released%3A%20Consensus%20Text%20Doesn%E2%80%99t%20Condemn%20Russia%20for%20Ukraine%20War%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClearly%2C%20this%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20blow%20to%20the%20United%20States%2C%20as%20the%20stern%20position%20adopted%20by%20Russia%20and%20China%20seems%20to%20have%20prevailed.%20It%20is%20a%20polarising%20issue%20and%20there%20are%20multiple%20views%20on%20this.%20There%20is%20a%20spectrum%20of%20views%20on%20this%2C%20so%20I%20think%20in%20all%20fairness%2C%20it%20was%20only%20right%20to%20record%20what%20was%20the%20reality%20in%20the%20meeting%20rooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CToday%E2%80%99s%20era%20must%20not%20be%20of%20war%2C%E2%80%9D%20in%20paragraph%2014%20appears%20to%20reflect%20what%20Narendra%20Modi%20had%20told%20President%20Putin%20at%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20Shanghai%20Cooperative%20Organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20Delhi%20G20%20leaders%20meeting%20is%20marked%20by%20major%20bilateral%20meetings%20at%20the%20Bharat%20Mandapam.%20A%20day%20before%20the%20meeting%2C%C2%A0India%20seems%20to%20have%20paid%20a%20significant%20price%20to%20Uncle%20Sam%20by%20providing%20market%20access%20to%20American%20poultry%20products%20by%20agreeing%20to%20reduce%20import%20tariffs%20to%20cancel%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organization%20(WTO)%20trade%20dispute.%20In%20normal%20times%2C%20India%20could%20have%20challenged%20the%20American%20position%20of%20complying%20with%20the%20Appellate%20Body%20recommendations.%20Instead%2C%20India%20chose%20to%20offer%20its%20market%20for%20allegedly%20disease-prone%20American%20poultry%20products%2C%20said%20a%20former%20Indian%20trade%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmpty%20promises%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apparent%20platitudinal%20and%20aspirational%20claims%20made%20in%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%20by%20the%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20his%20officials%20allegedly%20contained%20%E2%80%9Cempty%20promises%E2%80%9D%2C%20according%20to%20a%20senior%20official%20of%20a%20multilateral%20organisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F11155534%2FThe-Wire-4.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F11155534%2FThe-Wire-4.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F11155534%2FThe-Wire-4-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F11155534%2FThe-Wire-4-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-672548%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20with%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20other%20G20%20heads%20of%20state%20at%20Rajghat%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Sunday%2C%20September%2010%2C%202023.%20Photo%3A%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%2F%40narendramodi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20shocking%20that%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%20failed%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20of%20climate%20finance%20to%20enable%20developing%20countries%20reeling%20under%20continuing%20climate%20disasters%2C%20including%20the%20most%20critical%20issue%20of%20loss%20and%20damages%20as%20raised%20by%20the%20developing%20and%20poor%20countries%20at%20the%20COP%2027%20(Conference%20of%20Parties%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20Framework%20on%20Climate%20Change)%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20debt%20vulnerabilities%20faced%20by%20poor%20countries%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20official%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20G20%20or%20the%20Group%20of%2020%20industrialised%20and%20several%20developing%20countries%2C%20and%20now%20the%20new%20member%20African%20Union%2C%20is%20a%20premier%20economic%20forum%20that%20took%20birth%20at%20the%20end%20of%202008%20in%20the%20shadow%20of%20the%20financial%20crisis%20caused%20by%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20Wall%20Street%20and%20successive%20American%20policymakers%20%E2%80%93%20who%20did%20away%20with%20the%20Glass-Stegall%20Act%20of%201933.%20The%20G20%20comprises%20Argentina%2C%20Australia%2C%20Brazil%2C%20Canada%2C%20China%2C%20France%2C%20Germany%2C%20India%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20Italy%2C%20Japan%2C%20the%20Republic%20of%20Korea%2C%20Mexico%2C%20Russia%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20Turkey%2C%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20and%20the%20United%20States%20along%20with%20the%20European%20Union%20and%20now%20the%20African%20Union.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffive-keys-takeaways-from-the-g20-summit-in-delhi%5C%22%3EFive%20Keys%20Takeaways%20From%20the%20G20%20Summit%20in%20Delhi%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuccessive%20G20%20meetings%20merely%20added%20incremental%20language%20proposed%20by%20developing%20countries%20that%20faced%20fierce%20opposition%20from%20the%20United%20States%20and%20other%20major%20industrialised%20countries.%20Invariably%2C%20it%20is%20the%20Group%20of%20Seven%20industrialised%20countries%20that%20succeeded%20in%20including%20their%20priorities%20and%20initiatives%20while%20developing%20countries%20are%20apparently%20handed%20over%20brownie%20points%20in%20the%20final%20declaration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20unlimited%20hype%20and%20unstoppable%20chest-beating%20about%20holding%20the%20Presidency%20by%20India%2C%20the%20NDD%20seems%20to%20have%20rehashed%20the%20previous%20G20%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Statements%20with%20some%20inconsequential%20additions%20here%20and%20there%20with%20little%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20long%20Declaration%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20preamble%20to%20NDD%20contains%20a%20dozen%20grand%20pronouncements%20ranging%20from%20%E2%80%9Caccelerating%20strong%2C%20sustainable%2C%20balanced%20and%20inclusive%20growth%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20much-abandoned%20%E2%80%9Cfull%20and%20effective%20implementation%20of%20the%202023%20Agenda%20for%20Sustainable%20Development%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20scaling%20up%20financing%20for%20accelerating%20progress%20on%20SDGs%20(United%20Nations%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%E2%80%9D%20and%20reform%20of%20multilateral%20development%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20lack%20of%20binding%20nature%20of%20these%20pronouncements%2C%20there%20is%20little%20point%20in%20crowing%20about%20the%20NDD.%20Effectively%2C%20the%20language%20is%20phrased%20as%20we%20%E2%80%9Ccall%20on%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20commit%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20recognize%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20reaffirm%E2%80%9D%20and%20so%20on.%20It%20may%20not%20be%20out%20of%20place%20to%20call%20it%20a%20kind%20of%20blah%2C%20blah%2C%20blah%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NDD%20notes%20in%20paragraph%2016%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20uncertainty%20around%20the%20outlook%20remains%20high%E2%80%A6with%20notable%20tightening%20in%20global%20financial%20conditions%2C%20which%20could%20worsen%20debt%20vulnerability%2C%20persistent%20inflation%20and%20geoeconomic%20tensions%2C%20the%20balance%20of%20risks%20remains%20tilted%20to%20the%20downside%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20NDD%20failed%20to%20point%20the%20finger%20at%20one%20country%20that%20caused%20this%20macroeconomic%20crisis%2C%20namely%2C%20the%20continued%20hikes%20in%20interest%20rates%20which%20escalated%20the%20debt%20of%20poor%20countries%20by%20around%20%24%20800%20billion%20over%20the%20last%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twn.my%2Ftitle2%2Fwto.info%2F2023%2Fti230409.htm%5C%22%3Eyear%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20developing%20countries%20are%20already%20trapped%20in%20a%20vicious%20cycle%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdeepening%20distress%E2%80%9D%20that%20could%20ultimately%20result%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Clost%20decade%E2%80%9D%20for%20them%2C%20largely%20due%20to%20the%20recent%20high-interest%20rate%20hikes%20by%20the%20central%20banks%20of%20the%20developed%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUNCTAD%C2%A0(United%20Nations%20Conference%20on%20Trade%20and%20Development)%20said%20the%20deepening%20debt%20distress%20in%20developing%20countries%20could%20cause%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdevelopmental%20crisis%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%2039%20countries%20paying%20more%20to%20their%20external%20public%20creditors%20than%20what%20they%20received%20in%20new%20loans%2C%20with%20an%20adverse%20impact%20on%20public%20investments%20and%20social%20protection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESustainable%20development%20goals%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20easy%20to%20call%20for%20%E2%80%9Caccelerating%20progress%20on%20(UN%E2%80%99s%2017)%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%E2%80%9D%20that%20were%20launched%20in%202015%20and%20need%20to%20be%20complied%20fully%20by%202030.%20So%20far%2C%20around%2012%25%20of%20progress%20has%20been%20made%20in%20complying%20with%20the%2017%20goals%20that%20recognise%20%E2%80%9Cending%20poverty%20and%20other%20deprivations%20must%20go%20hand-in-hand%20with%20strategies%20that%20improve%20health%20and%20education%2C%20reduce%20inequality%2C%20and%20spur%20economic%20growth%20%E2%80%93%20all%20while%20tackling%20climate%20change%20and%20working%20to%20preserve%20our%20oceans%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsdgs.un.org%2Fgoals%5C%22%3Eforests%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20India%E2%80%99s%20track%20record%20of%20complying%20with%20the%20SDGs%20is%20anything%20but%20satisfactory.%20According%20to%20several%20studies%2C%20the%20number%20of%20people%20below%20the%20poverty%20line%20has%20substantially%20increased%20in%20the%20last%20four%20years%20following%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20grand%20pronouncements%20of%20%E2%80%9Crecommitting%20to%20achieving%20SDGs%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Celiminating%20hunger%20and%20malnutrition%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmacroeconomic%20impacts%20of%20food%20and%20energy%20insecurity%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20delivering%20quality%20education%20among%20others%2C%20will%20remain%20as%20empty%20promises%20if%20the%20host%20country%20for%20the%20G20%20meeting%20is%20unable%20to%20implement%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECulture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20India%20or%20Bharat%20is%20harking%20back%20to%20religion%20and%20religiosity%2C%20it%20is%20perhaps%20unsurprising%20that%20in%20paragraph%2031%2C%20specific%20language%20on%20%E2%80%9Cculture%20as%20a%20Transformative%20Driver%20of%20SDGs%E2%80%9D%20is%20inserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EClimate%20change%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20title%20of%20%E2%80%9CGreen%20Development%20Pact%20for%20a%20Sustainable%20Future%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20NDD%20includes%20specific%20language%20ostensibly%20to%20address%20climate%20change.%20It%20reiterates%20the%20specific%20objectives%20of%20the%20Paris%20Climate%20Change%20Agreement%20of%202015%2C%20including%20%E2%80%9Cits%20temperature%20goal%2C%20reflecting%20equity%20and%20the%20principle%20of%20common%20but%20differentiated%20responsibilities%20and%20respective%20capabilities%2C%20in%20light%20of%20different%20national%20circumstances%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F11122254%2Fli-an-lim-ycW4YxhrWHM-unsplash-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F11122254%2Fli-an-lim-ycW4YxhrWHM-unsplash-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F11122254%2Fli-an-lim-ycW4YxhrWHM-unsplash-1-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F11122254%2Fli-an-lim-ycW4YxhrWHM-unsplash-1-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-563686%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPlacard%20at%20a%20climate%20change%20protest%20in%20San%20Francisco.%20Photo%3A%20Unplash%2FLi-An%20Lim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20NDD%20turns%20a%20blind%20eye%20to%20unilateral%20carbon%20taxes%20that%20are%20going%20to%20be%20imposed%20by%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20the%20US%2C%20and%20other%20industrialised%20countries.%20In%20one%20go%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20much-boasted%20image%20of%20representing%20the%20Global%20South%20seems%20somewhat%20smudged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NDD%20appears%20to%20be%20on%20its%20weakest%20wicket%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20delivering%20on%20%E2%80%9Cclimate%20sustainable%20finance%E2%80%9D.%20Although%20it%20makes%20the%20right%20noises%20about%20implementing%20the%20previous%20Green%20Climate%20Fund%20and%20enhanced%20role%20of%20multilateral%20development%20banks%20in%20providing%20public%20finance%2C%20it%20meekly%20notes%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20need%20of%20USD%205.8-5.9%20trillion%20in%20the%20pre-2030%20period%20(as)%20required%20for%20developing%20countries%2C%20in%20particular%20for%20their%20needs%20to%20reach%20implement%20their%20NDCs%20(nationally%20determined%20contributions)%E2%80%9D.%20And%2C%20in%20the%20very%20next%20paragraph%2C%20it%20underscores%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccommitment%20made%20in%202010%20by%20the%20developed%20countries%20to%20mobilizing%20jointly%20USD%20100%20billion%20climate%20finance%20per%20year%20by%202020%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20now%2C%20industrialised%20countries%20that%20caused%20climate%20change%20have%20grossly%20failed%20to%20meet%20their%20commitments.%20Little%20wonder%20the%20vacuity%20of%20NDD%20stands%20exposed%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20climate%20finance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorse%20still%2C%20the%20industrialised%20countries%20are%20in%20no%20mood%20to%20relax%20their%20intellectual%20property%20rights%20on%20the%20rapid%20development%20of%20green%20technologies.%20It%20would%20be%20a%20misnomer%20to%20talk%20about%20effective%20aid%20and%20assistance%20coming%20from%20the%20US%20and%20other%20developed%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20perhaps%20the%20biggest%20failure%20of%20the%20G20%20meeting%20in%20New%20Delhi%20to%20remain%20conspicuously%20silent%20on%20the%20demand%20raised%20by%20many%20developing%20and%20poorest%20countries%20on%20loss%20and%20damages%20that%20was%20brought%20to%20the%20fore%20at%20the%20COP-27%20meeting%20in%20Sharam-el-Sheikh%20in%20Egypt%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20to%20%E2%80%9Cmultilateral%20institutions%20for%20the%2021%3Cspan%3Est%3C%2Fspan%3E%20century%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20NDD%20is%20replete%20with%20calls.%20It%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%2021st%20century%20also%20requires%20an%20international%20development%20finance%20system%20that%20is%20fit%C2%A0%20for%20purpose%2C%20including%20for%20the%20scale%20of%20need%20and%20depth%20of%20the%20shocks%20facing%20developing%20countries%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20the%20poorest%20and%20most%20vulnerable%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20working%20to%20deliver%20better%2C%20bigger%20and%20more%20effective%20MDBs%20by%20enhancing%20operating%20models%2C%20improving%20responsiveness%20and%20accessibility%2C%20and%20substantially%20increasing%20financing%20capacity%20to%20maximize%20development%20impact%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20reality%20on%20the%20ground%20is%20that%20the%20multilateral%20development%20banks%20are%20unable%20to%20provide%20finance%20to%20address%20current%20challenges%20stemming%20from%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20The%20Delhi%20Declaration%20says%20%E2%80%9CStronger%20MDBs%20will%20be%20important%20to%20our%20efforts%20to%20mobilize%20financing%20from%20all%20sources%20for%20a%20quantum%20jump%20from%20billions%20to%20trillions%20of%20dollars%C2%A0%20for%20development%E2%80%9D.%20It%20weakly%20underscores%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20need%20for%20enhancing%20representation%20and%20voice%20of%20developing%20countries%20in%20decision-making%20in%20global%20international%20economic%20and%20financial%20institutions%20in%20order%20to%20deliver%20more%20effective%2C%20credible%2C%20accountable%20and%20legitimate%20institutions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20calls%20for%20the%20international%20finance%20system%20to%20deliver%20significantly%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20financing%20to%20help%20developing%20countries%20and%20EMEs%20to%20fight%20poverty%2C%20tackle%20global%20challenges%20and%C2%A0%20maximise%20development%20impact%E2%80%9D%2C%20invariably%20remained%20as%20the%20proverbial%20Indian%20film%20%3Cem%3EKaaghaz%20ke%20Phool%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20only%20on%20paper%20since%20the%20first%20G20%20leaders%20meeting%20some%2015%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Fbyline%2Fravi-kanth-devarakonda%5C%22%3ERavi%20Kanth%20Devarakonda%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20senior%20journalist%20based%20in%20Geneva.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694482251000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F10175233%2FF5pyX8ua4AAoHu2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fno-real-gain-g20-delhi-declaration-offers-mere-lip-service-to-pressing-global-issues%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20the%20hype%20about%20India's%20G20%20presidency%2C%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%20seems%20to%20have%20rehashed%20the%20previous%20G20%20Leaders'%20Statements%20with%20some%20inconsequential%20additions%20here%20and%20there%20with%20little%20impact.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fno-real-gain-g20-delhi-declaration-offers-mere-lip-service-to-pressing-global-issues%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Flooding%20in%20Libya%20leaves%202%2C000%20people%20feared%20dead%2C%20many%20missing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694482090000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103591252%2Cimgsize-945787.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatim